profile_positions.description:
This position is responsible to support strategic, impactful and high-quality implementation of the coordination of Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) in Indonesia. Responsible to manage all aspects of the day to day tasks and management of SDGs activities, including:

1. Support the formulation of SGDs Indonesia documents (presidential decree, ministerial decree, metadata, reports, action plans, etc);
2. Establish cooperation with development partners (donor agency, international organization);
3. Consultation support for local government and counterparts;
4. Compose/formulate materials that related to SDGs for Indonesian officials;
5. Act as focal point/liaison for Secretariat SDGs and other counterparts (Government and Non-Government Actors);
6. Involved in event management that related to SDGs (Indonesia's side events in UN General Assembly, Islamic Development Bank Annual Meeting, IMF/World Bank Group Annual Meeting, High-Level Political Forum, etc);
7. Manage SDGs data; and
8. Other requested duties.

Junior Program Officer works closely with Implementing Team and  Working Groups in SDGs Indonesia National Coordination Team.

Main achievements:

1. Succeed to support the overall coordination and formulation of SDGs National Action Plan by Vice President of Republic of Indonesia
2. Managed to create concept, organise and establish cooperation with UNDP, ADB and JICA to hold SDGs parallel events on IMF-WBG Annual Meeting 2018 (Bali, 2018)


